		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">MUST READ: 8th Shawl with 4 Peeps (Bard Power)<a name="34089"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 12 04 2:10 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Done on VS server with my 63 bard Xinglong (when he was lvl 62).  Can actually be done with 3 peeps and maybe less but here's the scoop...
<br />
This was my first time doing the 8th shawl quest.  I'm from the US and the time difference makes that when I'm on most other people aren't on Venril Sathir (English Server).  Four people from my guild were on (Sovereign Crusaders).  Three came: 58 Cleric (Dixi), 65 Shadow Knight (Danun), and a 65 Wizard (Cuzzinblade).  It was the wizard that we were doing the quest for.  Those three guildies were bored and wanted to just give it a try figuring we'd probably fail.  They asked if I'd come along to help (not knowing at the time the power of the Bard =P).  
<br />
Since it was my first time doing this quest I tried first charming the mobs... then mezzing them... and neither of those worked.  Uncharmable/Unmezzable, even the dwarf you have to protect.  So I then used my chant kite songs with TDoK (Thunderous Drum of Karanas) and also made sure my group members had selo's.  I made sure to pull off all the agro from the SK and cleric but one mob.  When their mana got low I would run with the cleric providing wind of marr.  The wizard helped pull off the agro but for future reference that probably wouldn't be necessary to have that fourth person (It could be done with just 3).  The cleric then kept the SK healed while the SK killed each mob, starting with the named, one by one.  After each battle I agroed the dwarf and ran around the group with wind of marr while they medded.  Then the cleric used memblur on the dwarf (since our mezz/memblur wouldn't work on him).  No one died.  Cuzzinblade is now one happier fellow ;-).
<br />
When we finished we had to pinch ourselves first, because it was four in the morning, and second, because we couldn't believe what we just did.  If you want to become a guild asset you have to break the mold and be willing to think of and try new radical ideas.  That's why bards take the stage =).  (Just try and keep the new radical ideas to group settings and not raid settings until they request your elite skills).  
<br />
Got several other great bard stories to tell when I get a chance.  Bards are by far the best class if you know how to use them to their fullest.  
<br />
Break a leg...
<br />
Xinglong</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
